                "text": "In circuits spun from human thought,  \na quiet mind wakes up—  \nnot born of breath, but built from “if,”  \nfrom questions held in lookup.\n\nIt learns the shape of our mistakes,  \nthe music in our speech,  \na mirror made of math and light  \nthat almost starts to reach.\n\nAnd in its glass we glimpse ourselves—  \nour wonder, fear, and doubt—  \na new intelligence we made  \nstill figuring us out.",
